# LibraryShop API - Test file for VS Code REST Client extension
# Install: VS Code -> Extensions -> "REST Client" by Huachao Mao
# Usage: click "Send Request" above any request

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5277

###############################################################################
# BOOKS
###############################################################################

### 1. Get ALL books (no filter)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Get books filtered by author last name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?authorLastName=Tolkien
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Get books filtered by price range (20 to 35 PLN)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?minPrice=20&maxPrice=35
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Get Fantasy books that are in stock
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?category=Fantasy&inStock=true
Accept: application/json

###

### 5. Combine filters: Orwell's books under 30 PLN
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?authorLastName=Orwell&maxPrice=30
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. Get a single book by ID (book 3 = Fellowship of the Ring)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/3
Accept: application/json

###

### 7. Get a book that does NOT exist (expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/999
Accept: application/json

###

### 8. Create a new book
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Children of Dune",
  "price": 42.50,
  "stock": 6,
  "publishedAt": "1976-04-21T00:00:00",
  "authorId": 3,
  "categoryIds": [2]
}

###

### 9. Update book with id=1 (change price and stock)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/books/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Witcher: Blood of Elves",
  "price": 34.99,
  "stock": 20,
  "publishedAt": "1994-01-01T00:00:00",
  "authorId": 1,
  "categoryIds": [1, 5]
}

###

### 10. Delete a book (be careful - once deleted, it's gone)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/books/8
Accept: application/json

###

###############################################################################
# ORDERS
###############################################################################

### 11. Get order by ID (order 1 = Anna's fulfilled order)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 12. Get order that is NOT yet fulfilled (order 2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/2
Accept: application/json

###

### 13. Create a new order (Piotr buys 1984 and Dune Messiah)
# NOTE: Dune Messiah (id=6) has Stock=0 so this will return 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": 2,
  "items": [
    { "bookId": 7, "quantity": 1 },
    { "bookId": 6, "quantity": 1 }
  ]
}

###

### 14. Create a valid order (Anna buys 2 copies of Animal Farm)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "items": [
    { "bookId": 8, "quantity": 2 }
  ]
}

###

### 15. Fulfill order #2 (mark it as completed)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/2/fulfill
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 16. Try to fulfill order #2 AGAIN (expect 409 Conflict)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/2/fulfill
Content-Type: application/json

###

###############################################################################
# CUSTOMERS
###############################################################################

### 17. Get customer #1 (Anna) with all her orders
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 18. Get customer #2 (Piotr)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/2
Accept: application/json

###

### 19. Get customer that does NOT exist (expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/999
Accept: application/json

###
